1 Section 1. Section 13-2039, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 13-2039 (1)(a) A landfill may accept yard waste without condition
4 from December 1 through March 31 of each year.
5 (b) A landfill may accept yard waste year-round if such yard waste:
6 (i) Will be used for the production and recovery of methane gas for
7 use as fuel (A) with the approval of the department and (B) at a landfill
8 operating as a solid waste management facility with a permit issued
9 pursuant to the department's rules and regulations; or
10 (ii) Has been separated at its source from other solid waste and
11 will be used for the purpose of soil conditioning or composting.
12 (c) State and local governmental entities responsible for the
13 maintenance of public lands shall give preference to the use of composted
14 materials in all land maintenance activities. This section does not
15 prohibit the use of yard waste as land cover or as soil-conditioning
16 material.
17 (2) Land disposal of lead-acid batteries and waste oil is
18 prohibited.
19 (3)(a) Land disposal of waste tires in any form is prohibited except
20 tires that are nonrecyclable. For purposes of this subsection,
21 nonrecyclable tire means a press-on solid tire, a solid pneumatic shaped
22 tire, or a foam pneumatic tire.
23 (b) On and after September 1, 2003, placing or causing the placement
24 or disposal of scrap tires in any form into the waters of the state is
25 prohibited except as provided in section 13-2033.
26 (c) Tires are not considered disposed if they are (i) processed into
27 crumb rubber form and reused or recycled in manufactured products such
28 as, but not limited to, products used for schools, playgrounds, and
29 residential, lawn, and garden applications, (ii) used as safety barriers
30 for race courses for motorized vehicles, on the condition that the tires
31 are bolted together and properly wrapped, and not in loose, compressed,
