1 or baled form, (iii) used as tire-derived fuel, (iv) retreaded, (v)
2 processed into chip or shred form and used as drainage media in landfill
3 construction or septic drain fields, (vi) used as a raw material in
4 steelmaking, or (vii) processed into shred form and used as an
5 alternative daily cover in a landfill or for a civil engineering project
6 if such project is designed and constructed in compliance with the
7 Engineers and Architects Regulation Act and prior approval for such
8 project is obtained from the department by the tire shredder and the end
9 user, except that departmental approval is not necessary for a tire
10 project involving three thousand five hundred or fewer passenger tire
11 equivalents of waste tires if the department receives notification of the
12 project not later than thirty days prior to any construction on such
13 project. The notification shall contain the name and address of the tire
14 shredder and end user, the location of the project, a description of the
15 type of project, the number of passenger tire equivalents of waste tires
16 to be used, and any additional information the council determines is
17 necessary to accomplish the purposes of the Integrated Solid Waste
18 Management Act.
19 A race sponsor using tires as safety barriers pursuant to
20 subdivision (3)(c)(ii) of this section prior to October 1, 2006, shall
21 file an approved tire disposal plan with the department on or before
22 January 1, 2007. A race sponsor using tires as safety barriers on or
23 after October 1, 2006, shall file an approved tire disposal plan with the
24 department prior to the sponsor's first such use of tires. An approved
25 tire disposal plan shall provide for the disposal of tires which cease to
26 be used as safety barriers in accordance with subsection (3) of section
27 13-2033, and any such race sponsor who ceases to use tires as safety
28 barriers or whose facility ceases operation shall dispose of such tires
29 in accordance with his or her approved tire disposal plan. Any
30 modification to an approved tire disposal plan shall be submitted to and
31 approved by the department prior to implementation of such modified plan.
